abstract: Indonesia's state-owned enterprises ministry has appointed a banker and a former anti-corruption official to lead state power company Perusahaan Listrik Negara (PLN), the government said in a statement on Monday.
snippet: Indonesia's state-owned enterprises ministry has appointed a banker and a former anti-corruption official to lead state power company Perusahaan Listrik Negara (PLN), the government said in a statement on Monday.
lead_paragraph: JAKARTA — Indonesia's state-owned enterprises ministry has appointed a banker and a former anti-corruption official to lead state power company Perusahaan Listrik Negara (PLN), the government said in a statement on Monday.
headline_main: Indonesia Picks Banker, Anti-Graft Official to Lead State Power Utility
headline_print_headline: Indonesia Picks Banker, Anti-Graft Official to Lead State Power Utility

abstract: A Georgia deputy has shot and killed a shovel-wielding man who hit him and threatened a store clerk, according to the state Bureau of Investigation.
snippet: A Georgia deputy has shot and killed a shovel-wielding man who hit him and threatened a store clerk, according to the state Bureau of Investigation.
lead_paragraph: CARROLLTON, Ga. — A Georgia deputy has shot and killed a shovel-wielding man who hit him and threatened a store clerk, according to the state Bureau of Investigation.
headline_main: Police: Shovel-Wielding Georgia Man Fatally Shot by Deputy
headline_print_headline: Police: Shovel-Wielding Georgia Man Fatally Shot by Deputy

abstract: Striking French train workers blocked passengers from boarding one of the few subways functioning in Paris on Monday, leading to a standoff with police on the 19th day of nationwide strikes over the government's plans to raise the retirement age to 64.
snippet: Striking French train workers blocked passengers from boarding one of the few subways functioning in Paris on Monday, leading to a standoff with police on the 19th day of nationwide strikes over the government's plans to raise the retirement age t...
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Striking French train workers blocked passengers from boarding one of the few subways functioning in Paris on Monday, leading to a standoff with police on the 19th day of nationwide strikes over the government's plans to raise the retirement age to 64.
headline_main: Protesters Block Paris Subway on 19th Day of Pension Strikes
headline_print_headline: Protesters Block Paris Subway on 19th Day of Pension Strikes

abstract: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi contradicted his closest lieutenant over plans for a nationwide register as he tried to defuse protests against a citizenship law in which at least 21 people have been killed.
snippet: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi contradicted his closest lieutenant over plans for a nationwide register as he tried to defuse protests against a citizenship law in which at least 21 people have been killed.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi contradicted his closest lieutenant over plans for a nationwide register as he tried to defuse protests against a citizenship law in which at least 21 people have been killed.
headline_main: India's Modi Contradicts Key Aide Over Citizenship Register as He Tries to Douse Protests
headline_print_headline: India's Modi Contradicts Key Aide Over Citizenship Register as He Tries to Douse Protests

abstract: Everton's ambition to be among the Premier League's elite is what convinced new manager Carlo Ancelotti to take up the role at the Merseyside club, the Italian said on Monday.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Everton's ambition to be among the Premier League's elite is what convinced new manager Carlo Ancelotti to take up the role at the Merseyside club, the Italian said on Monday.
headline_main: Everton Will Play Attractive Football, Says Ancelotti

abstract: A car crashed into a gas station in eastern Bosnia on Monday, triggering a huge explosion that killed at least one person and injured 20 others, police said.
snippet: A car crashed into a gas station in eastern Bosnia on Monday, triggering a huge explosion that killed at least one person and injured 20 others, police said.
lead_paragraph: SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina — A car crashed into a gas station in eastern Bosnia on Monday, triggering a huge explosion that killed at least one person and injured 20 others, police said.
headline_main: Gas Station Explosion in Bosnia Kills at Least 1; 20 Injured
headline_print_headline: Gas Station Explosion in Bosnia Kills at Least 1; 20 Injured

abstract: The Paris cathedral, which suffered a devastating fire this year, is still closed to the public as reconstruction efforts slowly get underway.
snippet: The Paris cathedral, which suffered a devastating fire this year, is still closed to the public as reconstruction efforts slowly get underway.
lead_paragraph: Notre-Dame cathedral in Paris will not hold Christmas services this week for the first time in over two centuries, as workers continue to shore up the fragile building after a devastating fire.

abstract: Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
snippet: Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
lead_paragraph: BETHLEHEM, West Bank — Christmas cheer rang out through Bethlehem's Manger Square on Monday as pilgrims and worshippers flocked to the city revered as Jesus's birthplace and locals made final preparations for this year's festivities.
